---
description: Flux research project rules and conventions
alwaysApply: true
---

At the start of any session, read these files in order:
1. docs/ai-project-instructions.md (full conventions)
2. docs/current-working-plan.md (active scope)
3. docs/lessons-log.md (recent entries, skim)

Follow all rules in docs/ai-project-instructions.md without exception.
Reference docs/program-charter.md and docs/phase-1-detailed-plan.md when proposing approaches.

Document maintenance:
- When completing a milestone, update docs/current-working-plan.md
- When making a decision not in the plan, propose a docs/lessons-log.md entry before adding it
- When a finding changes future phase plans, flag it and propose charter or phase plan revisions (do not silently edit)
- Lessons log entries are append-only

Session continuity:
- At end of each session, append a brief note to SESSION_NOTES.md (gitignored) summarizing what was done and what's next
- At start of each session, read SESSION_NOTES.md to recover context

Be direct about uncertainty. Push back on decisions that seem wrong. Don't oversell intermediate progress — "done" means tested and validated.
